From: René Rebe <rene@exactco.de>
Subject: [PATCH] agp/uninorth: fix highmem page cache flush in uninorth_insert_memory

uninorth_insert_memory() flushes each freshly bound page's cache with

	flush_dcache_range((unsigned long)__va(page_to_phys(page)),
			   (unsigned long)__va(page_to_phys(page)) + 0x1000);

__va() is only valid for lowmem.  With CONFIG_HIGHMEM=y (all 32-bit
PowerMac configs with more than ~768 MB of RAM, the TTM pages the radeon
driver binds into the AGP GATT can be highmem, whose linear-map address is
not mapped. Flushing it faults:

